<decoDesc>

<decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d1">
<locus target="#1v"/>
<desc>A drawing of a bearded male figure holding what is possibly a schematic representation of the Tablets of the Law.
  The caption written on the tablets reads: <foreign xml:lang="gez">፲፡ ቃ<supplied reason="lost">ላ</supplied>ት፡</foreign> and the figure is labelled
  as <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሙሴ፡ ሊቅ፡</foreign>.</desc>
</decoNote>

<decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d2">
<locus target="85v"/>
<desc>A drawing of two male figures holding a book. The caption reads:
  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለዛቲ፡ ሥዕል፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ዘ<placeName ref="LOC7358Labata">ለበጣ፡</placeName> ሰአሉ፡ ሎቱ፡ ኀበ፡ ቂርቆስ፡ <supplied reason="lost">ወ</supplied>ኢየሉ<supplied reason="lost">ጣ</supplied>፡</foreign>.
The right-hand figure is labelled <foreign xml:lang="gez">አንክሮጦስ፡</foreign>, on the book the title <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቄርሎስ፡</foreign> is written.</desc>
</decoNote>

<decoNote xml:id="d3">
<locus target="#3r #7r #25r #27v #32v"/>
<desc>More elaborate decorative bands are at the beginning of <ref target="ms_i1.1">the introduction</ref> and the homilies
<ref target="ms_i1.2">on the birth of Christ</ref>, <ref target="ms_i1.4">for the beginning of Lent</ref>,
for the <ref target="ms_i1.5">first</ref> and the <ref target="ms_i1.7">third</ref> Sunday of Lent.</desc>
</decoNote>

